> seatbelts in there, people getting into the back seat
> might trip on them. Plus, I'd have to cut slits in the
> rubber floormat.
>
> Anyone have these mounted? Is tripping a problem?
> Or, has anyone mounted seatbelts (customly) to the
> framework of the middles seat? Like, to the rear leg
> of the seat?
> That way you could turn the middle seat around
> backwards (conference style) and people could still
